      <section eId="sec_38_470">
        <num>38.470</num>
        <content>
          <p>If the Kentucky National Guard or Kentucky active militia is called into state active duty by the Governor or into federal active duty by the President of the United States for any purpose, requiring the service of members who are students in any institution of learning in the state, no teacher, professor, principal, or president of the institution shall discriminate against the student by reason of his absence, but shall credit him with all academic work accomplished to the date of his absence. Students shall be given reasonable time to make up work missed as a result of a call to state or federal active duty.</p>
        </content>
